E(X^{n}) = \int_0^\infty n x^{n-1} P(\{X≥x\}) dx
R.H.S = \int_0^\infty n x^{n-1} P(\{X≥x\}) dx = \int_0^\infty n x^{n-1} (1-F(x)) dx
R.H.S = [x^{n}(1-F(x))]_0^\infty + \int_0^\infty x^{n} f(x) dx = 0 + \int_0^\infty x^{n} f(x) dx = E(X^{n})
